						<summary>

						<p>Pedestal of the bronze image of Vighnēśvara in the Chōlēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 18th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It refers to a gift made by Kanakāmba, wife of Muddu Veḷḷa-Koṇḍama Nāyaka, son of Toṇḍmaṇḍala Dhūli Rāghava Nāyaka of Kannappa-<hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> and also states the obeisance of Muddu Rāmabhadra Nāyaka.</p>						

						</summary>
